A 21-year-old Mpumalanga man allegedly confessed to having killed his 22 year old girlfriend during an argument, stuffing her body in a suitcase then burying it. The incident happened at Agincourt Village outside Thulamahashe, near Bushbuckridge. The man was arrested on June 22 after his family handed him over to the police following he alleged confession that he had killed his girlfriend and buried her in the yard. According to Mpumalanga police spokesperson Lieutenant Colonel Mtsholi Bhembe, the suspect's family took him to the police after he confessed to them that he had killed his girlfriend three months ago. It was at the police station that he gave more details. He allegedly told police that he hit his girlfriend with a blunt object on the head during a heated argument. Bhembe said the man also said after his girlfriend died, he put her lifeless body in a suitcase and buried it. The man then pointed police to where her had buried the body in the yard. Police dug the shallow grave and found the decomposed body. Bhembe added that the man appeared before the Mhala Magistrate Court on Monday and was remanded in custody pending a bail application. The Star